    ],
    investmentStrategy:"Crown PE governance model drives all investment decisions with measurable ROI, fast payback periods. Freyr must reframe from innovation partnership to tangible cost and revenue results with demonstrable ROI within 12-18 months. Entry sequencing: Head of RA → Schwartz (CLO) → Leffler (CFO) → Moiz (CEO).",
    strategicPriorities:[
      { priority:'MOST URGENT', title:'DAXXIFY EU/EMA Regulatory Authorisation', body:"FDA-approved since September 2022 — no EU authorisation after 3+ years. The EU aesthetics injectable market is $1.5B+. BOTOX and Dysport hold entrenched EU market positions while DAXXIFY has zero EU commercial revenue. Every additional month without EU approval is foregone revenue and worsening competitive position. Crown PE sponsors are accountable to this gap. No incumbent regulatory partner is serving this programme — Freyr has 850+ EU in-country affiliates and freya.intelligence EU regulatory intelligence with EMA pathway analysis. This is the single largest uncontested revenue opportunity in the Revance account.", freyrAction:"Initiate EU/EMA regulatory scoping with Head of RA immediately. Prepare DAXXIFY EMA programme proposal covering both glabellar lines and cervical dystonia indications. Demonstrate freya.intelligence EMA pathway analysis as the intelligence layer. Q3 2026.", nudgeSignal:"DAXXIFY EU gap now in its 4th year. EU aesthetics market estimated at $1.8B by 2027. BOTOX launched EU lifecycle extension Jan 2026. Every quarter of delay is market share surrendered permanently.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"This is Freyr's single most actionable opportunity in the Revance account. There is no incumbent. There is a named, confirmed regulatory gap. Freyr has the EU network and the freya.intelligence platform to own this programme. Initiate a regulatory scoping conversation with the Revance Head of Regulatory Affairs immediately." },
      { priority:'URGENT', title:'PV Programme Management — Cervical Dystonia Commercial Launch', body:"DAXXIFY cervical dystonia has been in commercial launch since May 2024 — creating a live, mandatory pharmacovigilance programme running right now. Botulinum toxin therapeutics carry significant adverse event complexity: dysphagia, dysphonia, muscular weakness, and systemic spread are all known AEs requiring ongoing ICSR processing, PSUR/PBRER authoring, signal detection, and REMS programme compliance under FDA 21 CFR 314. Botulinum toxin products carry a Black Box Warning — the highest level of FDA safety communication — which mandates a comprehensive Risk Management programme. There is currently no Freyr engagement anywhere in the Revance PV programme. Every quarter without Freyr in the PV conversation is a competitor entrenching or an un-served compliance obligation accumulating risk.", freyrAction:"Ask the Revance Regulatory Affairs or Medical Affairs contact a single direct question: 'Who is running your PV programme for cervical dystonia?' If no answer or dissatisfaction with current provider, Freyr PV proposal within one week: ICSR processing, PSUR authoring, signal detection, REMS compliance.", nudgeSignal:"Cervical dystonia PV programme has been running for 13+ months with no Freyr engagement confirmed. Botulinum toxin AE complexity includes Black Box Warning obligations — this is not a low-risk PV programme. Adjacent to existing RA relationship — lowest-friction cross-sell in the account.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"PV obligation exists today, is active, and should already have a vendor in place. If it does not, Freyr should be the answer. Starting now is not late — it is simply the next conversation." },
      { priority:'HIGH', title:'Crown PE Vendor Rationalisation and Cost Discipline', body:"Crown Laboratories' PE integration of Revance includes a full review of all inherited vendor contracts in H2 2026. The new CEO (Moiz), COO (Crowe), and CFO (Leffler) are Crown portfolio operators applying PE-portfolio criteria to every vendor: measurable ROI, short payback cycles, contract flexibility. Freyr's current single-service RA engagement is vulnerable to displacement in a rationalisation review unless Freyr expands to a multi-service footprint before the review cycle locks the vendor roster. Crown will consolidate to fewer, larger strategic partners. Freyr's Full-Service Model (Core + Growth + Technology) is the consolidation argument that Crown's PE governance will prioritise.", freyrAction:"Move to Full-Service Model commercial proposal before H2 2026 vendor review. Prepare Crown-compatible commercial terms: milestone-based payments, performance-linked outcomes, clear ROI model. Engage COO Crowe (operational validation) and CFO Leffler (budget approval) through Head of RA and Schwartz.", nudgeSignal:"Crown PE integration review timeline setting now. Freyr's single-service RA engagement is the minimum threshold for displacement. ICON/Parexel actively maintain relationships at Crown portfolio level.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"Freyr must be multi-service before the H2 2026 review cycle begins. One-service vendors get rationalised. Full-Service partners get retained and expanded." },
      { priority:'HIGH', title:'DAXXIFY China — NMPA Variation Management (Fosun Pharma)', body:"Fosun Pharma partnership for DAXXIFY development and commercialisation in China. NMPA submissions require country-specific regulatory variations, dossier adaptation for China-specific requirements, and HA management. CMC variation management workload is active as formulation evolves for the China market. NMPA variation management is a highly specific, country-unique regulatory challenge where Freyr's VIA (Variation Identification Agent) provides NMPA-specific variation recommendations natively — eliminating the manual NMPA guidance lookup process and reducing cycle time and cost per variation.", freyrAction:"Identify the Revance-side Fosun China partnership lead and CMC Director. Pitch VIA ROI for NMPA: variation cycle time reduction, cost per filing. PE-compatible ROI metric Crown governance will respond to. Proposal Q4 2026.", nudgeSignal:"Fosun NMPA programme active and progressing. VIA has no competitor equivalent for NMPA-specific variation management. Thomas Hitchcock (CInO) is the strategic sponsor for the China programme.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"VIA is the entry point to both the China programme and the Hitchcock (CInO) technology track relationship. Do not approach this as a regulatory services conversation — frame VIA as the NMPA intelligence platform that makes multi-geography variation management cost-predictable." },
      { priority:'MEDIUM', title:'Multi-Indication Regulatory Strategy — Phase II Pipeline', body:"DAXXIFY Phase II programmes for upper limb spasticity and plantar fasciitis represent Revance's pathway from a single-indication neurotoxin to a diversified therapeutics platform. Each indication requires an independent IND/NDA regulatory strategy distinct from the aesthetics and cervical dystonia regulatory pathways. CMC regulatory planning must also begin 12-18 months ahead of NDA filing as formulation changes compound variation management complexity. Phase II data readouts for spasticity and plantar fasciitis will generate IND/NDA planning urgency in H2 2026–2027.", freyrAction:"Approach Thomas Hitchcock (CInO) on Phase II regulatory complexity: 'As DAXXIFY moves into Phase II for upper limb spasticity and plantar fasciitis in parallel with the EU programme and Fosun China, how is the team managing variation management across multiple pathways and geographies?' Offer Regulatory Strategy Consulting + VIA multi-indication case study.", nudgeSignal:"Phase II active for two indications. IND/NDA planning should begin 12-18 months ahead — that window is now. Hitchcock is a PhD scientist who will engage on regulatory science substance, not operational pitching.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"This is the long-range R&D relationship entry point. Freyr's multi-indication regulatory strategy expertise + VIA for CMC variation management is the exact capability combination Hitchcock needs to build DAXXIFY's diversified therapeutics platform." },
      { priority:'ACTIVE', title:'DAXXIFY US Lifecycle Management — Post-Approval Maintenance', body:"Post-approval maintenance for both US DAXXIFY indications — annual reports, SPL labeling updates, REMS compliance, NDA supplement management. SUBMIT PRO for eCTD supplement publishing. LABEL 360 for structured labeling lifecycle management across aesthetics (glabellar lines) and cervical dystonia separate labels. REMS programme compliance support under FDA 21 CFR 314. This is the existing Freyr engagement anchor — protect, deepen, and use as the springboard to EU/EMA and PV expansion.", freyrAction:"Protect and deepen existing RA relationship. Expand scope to include SUBMIT PRO eCTD supplement publishing, LABEL 360 labeling lifecycle, and REMS compliance services. This is the relationship anchor for all Crown governance layer introductions.", nudgeSignal:"Existing RA relationship is Freyr's only current Revance foothold. Crown integration has not disrupted this engagement — yet. Head of RA is the anchor contact for all subsequent Crown governance introductions.", whatThisMeansForFreyr:"Do not take this relationship for granted post-Crown acquisition. The Head of RA relationship must be actively deepened and used as the bridge to the Crown executive governance layer. Every Freyr action at Revance runs through this contact." },
    ],
    nextBestAction:[
      { priority:'WEEK 1-2', action:'Verify Head of RA and re-engage on EU/EMA programme', detail:"Confirm whether Susanne Fors has moved to Ultragenyx (LinkedIn verification). Identify current Head of Regulatory Affairs. Send re-engagement email within 48 hours: 'DAXXIFY EU regulatory scoping — Freyr is ready to initiate the EMA authorisation programme. No incumbent. Ready now.' This single contact opens EU regulatory, PV, and Crown governance conversations simultaneously.", owner:'Account Lead', urgency:'Immediate' },
      { priority:'WEEK 1-2', action:"Ask the PV question — single sentence to unlock $3.6M", detail:"In the same or follow-up contact with Head of RA: 'We noticed DAXXIFY cervical dystonia launched commercially in May 2024 — who is currently managing the PV programme?' This is not a sales pitch. It is a single question. If there is a gap or dissatisfaction, have Freyr PV proposal ready to deliver within five business days.", owner:'Account Lead + PV Team', urgency:'Immediate' },
      { priority:'WEEK 2-4', action:'Deliver EU/EMA scoping brief with freya.intelligence demonstration', detail:"Prepare and deliver the DAXXIFY EU regulatory scoping document to Head of RA: Freyr EU affiliate network capability (850+ affiliates, direct EMA HA relationships), freya.intelligence EMA pathway analysis demonstration for DAXXIFY aesthetics authorisation, estimated timeline and programme structure for glabellar lines + cervical dystonia EMA dossier. This document opens the Crown governance conversation.", owner:'Account Lead + EU Reg Team', urgency:'Q3 2026' },
      { priority:'WEEK 3-5', action:'Propose 60-day freya.intelligence POC — no CEO sign-off required', detail:"Initiate 60-day freya.intelligence POC with the RA team: EU regulatory monitoring for DAXXIFY EMA preparation, BOTOX/Dysport EU label comparator analysis via Freya.KnowledgeGraphs, NMPA guidance tracking for Fosun programme. Approved at regulatory team level — does not require Crown CEO sign-off. Deliver weekly EU intelligence digest to build relationship with RA team.", owner:'Tech Sales', urgency:'Q3 2026' },
      { priority:'WEEK 4-6', action:'Request Kira Schwartz (CLO) introduction via Head of RA', detail:"After EU scoping brief delivered positively, request CLO introduction: 'Given the scale of the EU programme and Crown's compliance governance, we'd like to brief your CLO on Freyr's GxP compliance framework and how we protect Crown's regulatory compliance posture.' Prepare CLO Compliance Brief: freya fusion GxP validation documentation, audit trail architecture, PV compliance framework.", owner:'Senior BD Director', urgency:'Q3 2026' },
      { priority:'WEEK 5-7', action:'Hitchcock scientific outreach — VIA for multi-indication complexity', detail:"Targeted outreach to Thomas Hitchcock (CInO): 'As DAXXIFY moves into Phase II for upper limb spasticity and plantar fasciitis in parallel with the EU programme and Fosun China, how is the team managing variation management across multiple regulatory pathways and geographies?' Offer VIA NMPA case study for China programme. Technical peer register — not a sales call.", owner:'Account Lead + Tech Sales', urgency:'Q3-Q4 2026' },
      { priority:'WEEK 8-10', action:'Build and deliver Crown CEO Brief via Schwartz or Head of RA', detail:"Prepare one-page Crown CEO Brief: DAXXIFY EU revenue gap quantified in PE terms ($320M+ cumulative lost EU revenue), Freyr EU affiliate network capability, no incumbent confirmed, ROI estimate for EU programme vs. programme cost, vendor consolidation savings from Full-Service Model. Design for internal circulation by Schwartz or Head of RA to Moiz — not Freyr directly.", owner:'Senior BD Director + Account Lead', urgency:'Q3-Q4 2026' },
      { priority:'WEEK 8-10', action:'Prepare ROI model for Scott Leffler (CFO)', detail:"Build ROI model for Leffler before CFO meeting is requested: EU programme investment cost vs. EU revenue NPV over 5 years (EU aesthetics market $1.5B+, DAXXIFY realistic 5-10% share = $75-150M annually at maturity), PV programme cost vs. compliance risk exposure for botulinum toxin Black Box Warning obligation, vendor consolidation savings from Freyr Full-Service vs. fragmented alternative.", owner:'BD Director', urgency:'Q3-Q4 2026' },
    ],
