      nudgeSignal:'The revised Revance revenue target of $12–16M over three years is driven by three primary revenue drivers: EU/EMA regulatory services (multi-year programme for DAXXIFY authorisation), PV services (active commercial programme since May 2024), and Growth Services expansion (MLR, Medical Affairs). Technology entry adds incremental ARR. The base case assumes successful engagement with the Crown executive layer by Q3 2026.',
      whatThisMeansForFreyr:'The $12–16M 3-year target is achievable only if Freyr secures the EU/EMA regulatory services contract AND the PV programme in H2 2026. Missing either one drops the target by 35–50%. The Crown vendor review H2 2026 is the gating event — Freyr must be positioned as multi-service before that review begins.',
