    rightToWin:{
      nudgeSignal:"ICON plc, PRA Health Sciences (ICON-acquired), and Parexel all have active relationships with mid-tier specialty pharma companies at the Crown portfolio level. Crown Laboratories has historically used generalist CROs for clinical and regulatory outsourcing across its portfolio companies. Post-acquisition, Revance's procurement for regulatory services may be routed through Crown's preferred CRO panel rather than Revance-specific relationships.",
      whatThisMeansForFreyr:"Freyr needs a Crown-level relationship, not just a Revance-level relationship. Identify whether Crown has a preferred vendor panel or procurement framework across its portfolio companies. If so, Freyr must engage Crown's procurement or operations team to be included — before the next contract renewal cycle.",
      advantages:[
        { title:'EU Affiliate Network Depth', body:"For DAXXIFY's EU/EMA authorisation, Freyr's 850+ in-country EU affiliate network with direct HA relationships is unmatched by any generalist CRO. Parexel and ICON can file dossiers, but they do not have Freyr's depth of EU regulatory submission precedent in biologics and complex specialty injectables. The EU is Freyr's home ground. This is not a competitive battle Freyr should lose." },
        { title:'VIA Has No Equivalent for NMPA Variation Management', body:"Revance's China Fosun partnership requires NMPA-specific variation management as DAXXIFY is developed and adapted for the China market. VIA (Variation Identification Agent) provides authority- and country-specific variation recommendations that no other platform delivers natively. ICON and Parexel would execute this manually through regulatory consultants. VIA turns it into a structured, trackable, cost-predictable workflow — exactly the language Crown's PE governance will respond to." },
        { title:'PV Adjacent to Existing RA Relationship', body:"Freyr has an existing regulatory services relationship at Revance. Introducing Freyr PV services to the same Regulatory Affairs and Medical Affairs contacts is the lowest-friction cross-sell in any account. There is no new relationship to build — there is only a conversation to have. The PV programme has been running since the cervical dystonia commercial launch in May 2024." },
        { title:"Crown PE ROI Language", body:"Freyr's Full-Service Model, spanning Core Services, Growth Services, and Technology, is uniquely positioned to deliver the vendor consolidation narrative that Crown's PE governance will prioritise. Being the single regulatory partner across all service and technology categories is the consolidation argument Freyr must make to Crown's operational leadership. No other regulatory firm has this breadth across services and technology simultaneously." },
      ],
