    actionPlan90Day:{
      nudgeSignal:'Actions 1 and 2 — EU/EMA scoping and PV — are not next quarter objectives. They are next two weeks. The EU gap has existed for three years and the PV programme has been running for over two years without Freyr. Both are active needs with no confirmed Freyr presence. Every month of further delay is revenue and margin held by someone else.',
      whatThisMeansForFreyr:"The Crown vendor rationalisation review begins in H2 2026 — Freyr must be multi-service before that review locks the vendor roster.",
      steps:[
        { weeks:'1–2', action:'Verify Head of RA and re-engage', detail:"Confirm current Head of Regulatory Affairs — verify whether Susanne Fors has moved to Ultragenyx. Re-engagement email immediately: EU/EMA DAXXIFY scoping as the opening agenda. This is Freyr's anchor contact for all subsequent actions.", owner:'Account Lead', metric:'RA contact confirmed and re-engagement email sent' },
        { weeks:'1–2', action:'Open PV conversation', detail:'Ask Head of RA: "We noticed DAXXIFY cervical dystonia launched commercially in May 2024 — who is managing the PV programme currently?" This is a single question. If there is a gap or dissatisfaction, have Freyr PV proposal ready to deliver within one week.', owner:'Account Lead + PV Team', metric:'PV question asked; PV status known' },
        { weeks:'2–4', action:'Deliver EU/EMA scoping brief', detail:"Prepare and deliver DAXXIFY EU regulatory scoping document to Head of RA: Freyr EU affiliate network capability, freya.intelligence EMA pathway analysis demonstration, estimated timeline and programme structure for DAXXIFY glabellar lines + cervical dystonia EMA dossier. This is the document that opens the Crown governance conversation.", owner:'Account Lead + EU Reg Team', metric:'EU scoping brief delivered and meeting scheduled' },
        { weeks:'3–5', action:'Initiate freya.intelligence POC', detail:"Propose 60-day freya.intelligence POC to Head of RA: EU regulatory monitoring for DAXXIFY EMA preparation, BOTOX/Dysport EU label comparator analysis. Approved at regulatory team level — does not require CEO sign-off. Deliver weekly EU intelligence digest.", owner:'Tech Sales', metric:'POC live; weekly digest delivered' },
        { weeks:'4–6', action:'Request Schwartz introduction via RA', detail:"After EU scoping brief delivered positively, request CLO introduction: 'Given the scale of the EU programme and Crown's compliance governance, we'd like to brief your CLO on Freyr's GxP compliance framework.' Prepare compliance brief for Schwartz: freya fusion GxP validation, audit trail architecture, PV compliance framework.", owner:'Senior BD Director', metric:'Schwartz meeting confirmed' },
        { weeks:'5–7', action:'Hitchcock scientific outreach', detail:"Targeted outreach to Thomas Hitchcock (CInO) on DAXXIFY Phase II regulatory complexity: 'As DAXXIFY moves into Phase II for upper limb spasticity and plantar fasciitis in parallel with the EU programme and Fosun China, how is the team managing variation management across multiple pathways and geographies?' Offer VIA NMPA case study.", owner:'Account Lead + Tech Sales', metric:'Hitchcock meeting confirmed' },
        { weeks:'6–8', action:'Deliver PV proposal (if gap confirmed)', detail:"If PV question confirms no incumbent or dissatisfaction: Freyr PV proposal delivered within five business days. Scope: ICSR processing, PSUR authoring, signal detection, REMS compliance for cervical dystonia commercial programme. Adjacent to existing RA relationship — no new relationship required.", owner:'PV Team + Account Lead', metric:'PV proposal delivered; RFP or scoping call initiated' },
        { weeks:'8–10', action:'Crown CEO Brief preparation', detail:"Build one-page Crown CEO Brief: DAXXIFY EU revenue gap quantified in PE terms, Freyr EU capability and timeline, PV compliance programme framing, vendor consolidation ROI model. Design for Schwartz or Head of RA to deliver to Moiz, not Freyr directly.", owner:'Senior BD Director + Account Lead', metric:'CEO Brief completed and delivered to RA or Schwartz' },
        { weeks:'8–10', action:'CFO ROI model development', detail:'Build ROI model for Leffler: EU programme investment vs. EU revenue NPV over 5 years, PV programme cost vs. compliance risk exposure, vendor consolidation savings from Freyr Full-Service vs. fragmented alternative. Have ready before CFO meeting is requested.', owner:'BD Director', metric:'ROI model completed' },
        { weeks:'10–12', action:'Crown executive meeting (CEO or CFO)', detail:'Via Schwartz or RA: request brief executive introduction to Moiz (CEO) or Leffler (CFO). Lead with EU revenue opportunity (CFO framing) or vendor consolidation argument (COO framing). Senior Freyr BD leadership required.', owner:'Senior BD Director', metric:'Crown executive meeting held' },
        { weeks:'12–13', action:'90-Day Review', detail:'Internal Freyr review: RA contact status, PV engagement status, freya.intelligence POC outcome, Schwartz/Hitchcock engagement progress, Crown executive meeting outcome. Revise FY2027 account plan. Set Q4 2026 objectives.', owner:'Account Lead + BD Director', metric:'90-day review completed; Q4 plan set' },
      ],
